{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":820,"text":"Roy Price is a man that most of you\nhave probably never heard about,"},{"time":5120,"text":"even though he may have been responsible"},{"time":7640,"text":"for 22 somewhat mediocre \nminutes of your life on April 19, 2013."},{"time":14560,"text":"He may have also been responsible\nfor 22 very entertaining minutes,"},{"time":17760,"text":"but not very many of you."},{"time":20040,"text":"And all of that goes back to a decision"},{"time":21960,"text":"that Roy had to make\nabout three years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23984,"text":"So you see, Roy Price\nis a senior executive with Amazon Studios."},{"time":28840,"text":"That's the TV production\ncompany of Amazon."},{"time":31880,"text":"He's 47 years old, slim, spiky hair,"},{"time":35160,"text":"describes himself on Twitter\nas \"movies, TV, technology, tacos.\""},{"time":40000,"text":"And Roy Price has a very responsible job,\nbecause it's his responsibility"},{"time":45200,"text":"to pick the shows, the original content\nthat Amazon is going to make."},{"time":49280,"text":"And of course that's\na highly competitive space."},{"time":51640,"text":"I mean, there are so many\nTV shows already out there,"},{"time":54400,"text":"that Roy can't just choose any show."},{"time":56600,"text":"He has to find shows\nthat are really, really great."},{"time":60720,"text":"So in other words, he has to find shows"},{"time":63560,"text":"that are on the very right end\nof this curve here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65960,"text":"So this curve here\nis the rating distribution"},{"time":68640,"text":"of about 2,500 TV shows\non the website IMDB,"},{"time":73040,"text":"and the rating goes from one to 10,"},{"time":75960,"text":"and the height here shows you\nhow many shows get that rating."},{"time":78960,"text":"So if your show gets a rating\nof nine points or higher, that's a winner."},{"time":83680,"text":"Then you have a top two percent show."},{"time":85520,"text":"That's shows like \"Breaking Bad,\"\n\"Game of Thrones,\" \"The Wire,\""},{"time":89440,"text":"so all of these shows that are addictive,"},{"time":91760,"text":"whereafter you've watched a season,\nyour brain is basically like,"},{"time":94840,"text":"\"Where can I get more of these episodes?\""},{"time":97040,"text":"That kind of show."},{"time":98920,"text":"On the left side, just for clarity,\nhere on that end,"},{"time":101440,"text":"you have a show called\n\"Toddlers and Tiaras\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107320,"text":"-- which should tell you enough"},{"time":108880,"text":"about what's going on\non that end of the curve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111095,"text":"Now, Roy Price is not worried about\ngetting on the left end of the curve,"},{"time":115280,"text":"because I think you would have to have\nsome serious brainpower"},{"time":118240,"text":"to undercut \"Toddlers and Tiaras.\""},{"time":119960,"text":"So what he's worried about\nis this middle bulge here,"},{"time":123920,"text":"the bulge of average TV,"},{"time":125760,"text":"you know, those shows\nthat aren't really good or really bad,"},{"time":128639,"text":"they don't really get you excited."},{"time":130320,"text":"So he needs to make sure\nthat he's really on the right end of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135200,"text":"So the pressure is on,"},{"time":136800,"text":"and of course it's also the first time"},{"time":139000,"text":"that Amazon is even\ndoing something like this,"},{"time":141200,"text":"so Roy Price does not want\nto take any chances."},{"time":144560,"text":"He wants to engineer success."},{"time":147040,"text":"He needs a guaranteed success,"},{"time":148840,"text":"and so what he does is,\nhe holds a competition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151440,"text":"So he takes a bunch of ideas for TV shows,"},{"time":154600,"text":"and from those ideas,\nthrough an evaluation,"},{"time":156920,"text":"they select eight candidates for TV shows,"},{"time":161040,"text":"and then he just makes the first episode\nof each one of these shows"},{"time":164280,"text":"and puts them online for free\nfor everyone to watch."},{"time":167440,"text":"And so when Amazon\nis giving out free stuff,"},{"time":169720,"text":"you're going to take it, right?"},{"time":171280,"text":"So millions of viewers\nare watching those episodes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176440,"text":"What they don't realize is that,\nwhile they're watching their shows,"},{"time":179680,"text":"actually, they are being watched."},{"time":182000,"text":"They are being watched\nby Roy Price and his team,"},{"time":184360,"text":"who record everything."},{"time":185760,"text":"They record when somebody presses play,\nwhen somebody presses pause,"},{"time":189160,"text":"what parts they skip,\nwhat parts they watch again."},{"time":191720,"text":"So they collect millions of data points,"},{"time":194000,"text":"because they want\nto have those data points"},{"time":196120,"text":"to then decide\nwhich show they should make."},{"time":198840,"text":"And sure enough,\nso they collect all the data,"},{"time":201040,"text":"they do all the data crunching,\nand an answer emerges,"},{"time":203640,"text":"and the answer is,"},{"time":204880,"text":"\"Amazon should do a sitcom\nabout four Republican US Senators.\""},{"time":210440,"text":"They did that show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211680,"text":"So does anyone know the name of the show?"},{"time":214720,"text":"(Audience: \"Alpha House.\")"},{"time":216040,"text":"Yes, \"Alpha House,\""},{"time":217520,"text":"but it seems like not too many of you here\nremember that show, actually,"},{"time":221640,"text":"because it didn't turn out that great."},{"time":223520,"text":"It's actually just an average show,"},{"time":225400,"text":"actually -- literally, in fact, because\nthe average of this curve here is at 7.4,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and \"Alpha House\" lands at 7.5,"},{"time":232440,"text":"so a slightly above average show,"},{"time":234480,"text":"but certainly not what Roy Price\nand his team were aiming for."},{"time":238320,"text":"Meanwhile, however,\nat about the same time,"},{"time":241200,"text":"at another company,"},{"time":242800,"text":"another executive did manage\nto land a top show using data analysis,"},{"time":247040,"text":"and his name is Ted,"},{"time":248640,"text":"Ted Sarandos, who is\nthe Chief Content Officer of Netflix,"},{"time":252080,"text":"and just like Roy,\nhe's on a constant mission"},{"time":254240,"text":"to find that great TV show,"},{"time":255760,"text":"and he uses data as well to do that,"},{"time":257800,"text":"except he does it\na little bit differently."},{"time":259839,"text":"So instead of holding a competition,\nwhat he did -- and his team of course --"},{"time":263600,"text":"was they looked at all the data\nthey already had about Netflix viewers,"},{"time":267160,"text":"you know, the ratings\nthey give their shows,"},{"time":269280,"text":"the viewing histories,\nwhat shows people like, and so on."},{"time":272000,"text":"And then they use that data to discover"},{"time":273920,"text":"all of these little bits and pieces\nabout the audience:"},{"time":276560,"text":"what kinds of shows they like,"},{"time":278040,"text":"what kind of producers,\nwhat kind of actors."},{"time":280160,"text":"And once they had\nall of these pieces together,"},{"time":282760,"text":"they took a leap of faith,"},{"time":284440,"text":"and they decided to license"},{"time":286560,"text":"not a sitcom about four Senators"},{"time":289040,"text":"but a drama series about a single Senator."},{"time":292760,"text":"You guys know the show?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295760,"text":"Yes, \"House of Cards,\" and Netflix\nof course, nailed it with that show,"},{"time":299520,"text":"at least for the first two seasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301680,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305680,"text":"\"House of Cards\" gets\na 9.1 rating on this curve,"},{"time":308880,"text":"so it's exactly\nwhere they wanted it to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312080,"text":"Now, the question of course is,\nwhat happened here?"},{"time":314520,"text":"So you have two very competitive,\ndata-savvy companies."},{"time":317200,"text":"They connect all of these\nmillions of data points,"},{"time":320080,"text":"and then it works\nbeautifully for one of them,"},{"time":322480,"text":"and it doesn't work for the other one."},{"time":324360,"text":"So why?"},{"time":325600,"text":"Because logic kind of tells you\nthat this should be working all the time."},{"time":329080,"text":"I mean, if you're collecting\nmillions of data points"},{"time":331560,"text":"on a decision you're going to make,"},{"time":333320,"text":"then you should be able\nto make a pretty good decision."},{"time":335960,"text":"You have 200 years\nof statistics to rely on."},{"time":338200,"text":"You're amplifying it\nwith very powerful computers."},{"time":341240,"text":"The least you could expect\nis good TV, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345880,"text":"And if data analysis\ndoes not work that way,"},{"time":349520,"text":"then it actually gets a little scary,"},{"time":351600,"text":"because we live in a time\nwhere we're turning to data more and more"},{"time":355440,"text":"to make very serious decisions\nthat go far beyond TV."},{"time":360760,"text":"Does anyone here know the company\nMulti-Health Systems?"},{"time":365080,"text":"No one. OK, that's good actually."},{"time":366760,"text":"OK, so Multi-Health Systems\nis a software company,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and I hope that nobody here in this room"},{"time":372840,"text":"ever comes into contact\nwith that software,"},{"time":376040,"text":"because if you do,\nit means you're in prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379360,"text":"If someone here in the US is in prison,\nand they apply for parole,"},{"time":382920,"text":"then it's very likely that\ndata analysis software from that company"},{"time":387240,"text":"will be used in determining\nwhether to grant that parole."},{"time":390880,"text":"So it's the same principle\nas Amazon and Netflix,"},{"time":393480,"text":"but now instead of deciding whether\na TV show is going to be good or bad,"},{"time":398120,"text":"you're deciding whether a person\nis going to be good or bad."},{"time":401040,"text":"And mediocre TV, 22 minutes,\nthat can be pretty bad,"},{"time":406560,"text":"but more years in prison,\nI guess, even worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410360,"text":"And unfortunately, there is actually\nsome evidence that this data analysis,"},{"time":414520,"text":"despite having lots of data,\ndoes not always produce optimum results."},{"time":418760,"text":"And that's not because a company\nlike Multi-Health Systems"},{"time":421506,"text":"doesn't know what to do with data."},{"time":423158,"text":"Even the most data-savvy\ncompanies get it wrong."},{"time":425480,"text":"Yes, even Google gets it wrong sometimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428680,"text":"In 2009, Google announced\nthat they were able, with data analysis,"},{"time":433200,"text":"to predict outbreaks of influenza,\nthe nasty kind of flu,"},{"time":437360,"text":"by doing data analysis\non their Google searches."},{"time":441160,"text":"And it worked beautifully,\nand it made a big splash in the news,"},{"time":445040,"text":"including the pinnacle\nof scientific success:"},{"time":447200,"text":"a publication in the journal \"Nature.\""},{"time":449680,"text":"It worked beautifully\nfor year after year after year,"},{"time":453320,"text":"until one year it failed."},{"time":455000,"text":"And nobody could even tell exactly why."},{"time":457280,"text":"It just didn't work that year,"},{"time":459000,"text":"and of course that again made big news,"},{"time":460960,"text":"including now a retraction"},{"time":462600,"text":"of a publication\nfrom the journal \"Nature.\""},{"time":466480,"text":"So even the most data-savvy companies,\nAmazon and Google,"},{"time":469840,"text":"they sometimes get it wrong."},{"time":472000,"text":"And despite all those failures,"},{"time":474960,"text":"data is moving rapidly\ninto real-life decision-making --"},{"time":478840,"text":"into the workplace,"},{"time":480680,"text":"law enforcement,"},{"time":482520,"text":"medicine."},{"time":484400,"text":"So we should better make sure\nthat data is helping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487760,"text":"Now, personally I've seen\na lot of this struggle with data myself,"},{"time":490920,"text":"because I work in computational genetics,"},{"time":492920,"text":"which is also a field\nwhere lots of very smart people"},{"time":495440,"text":"are using unimaginable amounts of data\nto make pretty serious decisions"},{"time":499120,"text":"like deciding on a cancer therapy\nor developing a drug."},{"time":503520,"text":"And over the years,\nI've noticed a sort of pattern"},{"time":505920,"text":"or kind of rule, if you will,\nabout the difference"},{"time":508400,"text":"between successful\ndecision-making with data"},{"time":511120,"text":"and unsuccessful decision-making,"},{"time":512760,"text":"and I find this a pattern worth sharing,\nand it goes something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518520,"text":"So whenever you're\nsolving a complex problem,"},{"time":520679,"text":"you're doing essentially two things."},{"time":522440,"text":"The first one is, you take that problem\napart into its bits and pieces"},{"time":525760,"text":"so that you can deeply analyze\nthose bits and pieces,"},{"time":528280,"text":"and then of course\nyou do the second part."},{"time":530320,"text":"You put all of these bits and pieces\nback together again"},{"time":533000,"text":"to come to your conclusion."},{"time":534360,"text":"And sometimes you\nhave to do it over again,"},{"time":536720,"text":"but it's always those two things:"},{"time":538400,"text":"taking apart and putting\nback together again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542280,"text":"And now the crucial thing is"},{"time":543920,"text":"that data and data analysis"},{"time":546840,"text":"is only good for the first part."},{"time":549360,"text":"Data and data analysis,\nno matter how powerful,"},{"time":551600,"text":"can only help you taking a problem apart\nand understanding its pieces."},{"time":556080,"text":"It's not suited to put those pieces\nback together again"},{"time":559600,"text":"and then to come to a conclusion."},{"time":561520,"text":"There's another tool that can do that,\nand we all have it,"},{"time":564280,"text":"and that tool is the brain."},{"time":565600,"text":"If there's one thing a brain is good at,"},{"time":567560,"text":"it's taking bits and pieces\nback together again,"},{"time":569840,"text":"even when you have incomplete information,"},{"time":571880,"text":"and coming to a good conclusion,"},{"time":573480,"text":"especially if it's the brain of an expert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576440,"text":"And that's why I believe\nthat Netflix was so successful,"},{"time":579120,"text":"because they used data and brains\nwhere they belong in the process."},{"time":582720,"text":"They use data to first understand\nlots of pieces about their audience"},{"time":586280,"text":"that they otherwise wouldn't have\nbeen able to understand at that depth,"},{"time":589720,"text":"but then the decision\nto take all these bits and pieces"},{"time":592360,"text":"and put them back together again\nand make a show like \"House of Cards,\""},{"time":595720,"text":"that was nowhere in the data."},{"time":597160,"text":"Ted Sarandos and his team\nmade that decision to license that show,"},{"time":601160,"text":"which also meant, by the way,\nthat they were taking"},{"time":603565,"text":"a pretty big personal risk\nwith that decision."},{"time":606440,"text":"And Amazon, on the other hand,\nthey did it the wrong way around."},{"time":609480,"text":"They used data all the way\nto drive their decision-making,"},{"time":612240,"text":"first when they held\ntheir competition of TV ideas,"},{"time":614680,"text":"then when they selected \"Alpha House\"\nto make as a show."},{"time":618400,"text":"Which of course was\na very safe decision for them,"},{"time":620920,"text":"because they could always\npoint at the data, saying,"},{"time":623400,"text":"\"This is what the data tells us.\""},{"time":625120,"text":"But it didn't lead to the exceptional\nresults that they were hoping for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630120,"text":"So data is of course a massively\nuseful tool to make better decisions,"},{"time":635120,"text":"but I believe that things go wrong"},{"time":637520,"text":"when data is starting\nto drive those decisions."},{"time":640120,"text":"No matter how powerful,\ndata is just a tool,"},{"time":643920,"text":"and to keep that in mind,\nI find this device here quite useful."},{"time":647280,"text":"Many of you will ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649760,"text":"Before there was data,"},{"time":651000,"text":"this was the decision-making\ndevice to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655160,"text":"Many of you will know this."},{"time":656520,"text":"This toy here is called the Magic 8 Ball,"},{"time":658497,"text":"and it's really amazing,"},{"time":659720,"text":"because if you have a decision to make,\na yes or no question,"},{"time":662640,"text":"all you have to do is you shake the ball,\nand then you get an answer --"},{"time":666400,"text":"\"Most Likely\" -- right here\nin this window in real time."},{"time":669240,"text":"I'll have it out later for tech demos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":672600,"text":"Now, the thing is, of course --\nso I've made some decisions in my life"},{"time":676200,"text":"where, in hindsight,\nI should have just listened to the ball."},{"time":679120,"text":"But, you know, of course,\nif you have the data available,"},{"time":682480,"text":"you want to replace this with something\nmuch more sophisticated,"},{"time":685560,"text":"like data analysis\nto come to a better decision."},{"time":689200,"text":"But that does not change the basic setup."},{"time":691840,"text":"So the ball may get smarter\nand smarter and smarter,"},{"time":695040,"text":"but I believe it's still on us\nto make the decisions"},{"time":697880,"text":"if we want to achieve\nsomething extraordinary,"},{"time":700920,"text":"on the right end of the curve."},{"time":702880,"text":"And I find that a very encouraging\nmessage, in fact,"},{"time":707400,"text":"that even in the face\nof huge amounts of data,"},{"time":711400,"text":"it still pays off to make decisions,"},{"time":715520,"text":"to be an expert in what you're doing"},{"time":718200,"text":"and take risks."},{"time":720320,"text":"Because in the end, it's not data,"},{"time":723120,"text":"it's risks that will land you\non the right end of the curve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727840,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729080,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}